(165, 'Dhairen - 2026-02-02: Cash/AP had interacted last time around - view was that founders were opportunistic (original plan was fashion, then jumped to stablecoin trendline). Spoke to Saloni this morning - quite positive on the founders compounding. White has invested. Company has pivoted to stablecoin cards with early traction through a reseller model. General interest in spending time given traction in Kast, Aspora etc. Company has moved to global GTM now - unclear what''s the RTW/RTP. Founders in Bangalore Feb 4-6 to meet people. Dhairen wants to join if we''re meeting, or can set up separately.'),
(166, 'Rajat reflections - SM for $100K: ?? Key Q: GTM chops || PDF conversion ++ Clear Why Now because of Tech improvements & AI FOMO ++ Very Spiky || walked in negative - very intelligent folks ++ Product seemed interesting ++ Potential to go viral like Quizziz ++ Superior to the OpenNote team; much better product ++ Clear why now - given this is a P0 problem for every teacher ?? Very raw on GTM || going to be a crowded market ?? Roadblocks from a product adoption lens - if they can integrate into LMS and automate the PDF creation - it could be a game changer ?? Product does get commoditized - but no one will build at their pace
Product & Market Strategy: - Current focus: Math grading with instant feedback and error identification - Processing: Parallel agents handle hundreds of worksheets simultaneously - Vision: “Agile learning” - zero-cost grading/lesson planning enabling personalized learning journeys - Go-to-market approach: - Key market timing advantages:
Heads Up Note 2025-08-26: Hi team, Sharing the heads-up note for our investment in Frizzle Frizzle is an AI-powered solution for grading handwritten math worksheets. The platform helps teachers save 10-15 hours per week on grading while creating a faster feedback loop for students. The founders position their solution as enabling "agile learning" compared to the current "waterfall" approach in education where students wait weeks for feedback. DeVC is investing $100K as part of a YC SAFE round (more details) below Note: deck...'),
(167, '(1) Founders and Key Team: Name – Shrey Doshi – Title - Career snapshot (one-line): BBA in Marketing;Entrepreneurship background; family business in pharmaceutical exports; roles in media sales, digital marketing, and FMCG sales. - Functional responsibility in current venture: Sales, marketing, and related GTM activities (as indicated by roles such as Head of Sales - FMCG and related marketing leadership). - Equity % (if stated) and commitment: Not disclosed. - Relevance of prior experience: Strong in marketing, sales, and distribution channels, which are relevant for consumer wellness product GTM in India; explicit domain experience in FMCG and pharmaceutical exports may aid distribution and partnerships.
Company Snapshot: Problem & solution - Problem: Nutrition does not equal absorption; a large portion of the population has impaired nutrient processing (BCMO1 variant, MTHFR variant), with 48% unable to convert plant carotene to Vitamin A and up to 70% of people needing more supplements/higher dosages without seeing a difference. This aligns with India’s nutrition paradox and demand for more effective, bioavailable solutions. - Solution: A Spirulina-based super algae formulation marketed as having high bioavailability and broad health benefits (anti-aging, anti-inflammatory, immunity, liver and gut health, etc.). Core ingredients cited include Spirulina, chlorophyll, phycocyanin, and carotenoids. Claims include improved nutrient bioavailability and multiple health outcomes ...'),
